{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1928,"text":"So ... we're in a real live war\nat the moment,"},{"time":6017,"text":"and it's a war that we're truly losing."},{"time":8970,"text":"It's a war on superbugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13692,"text":"So you might wonder,"},{"time":15547,"text":"if I'm going to talk about superbugs,"},{"time":17629,"text":"why I'm showing you a photograph\nof some soccer fans --"},{"time":21885,"text":"Liverpool soccer fans\ncelebrating a famous victory"},{"time":25130,"text":"in Istanbul, a decade ago."},{"time":28233,"text":"In the back, in the red shirt,"},{"time":30417,"text":"well, that's me,"},{"time":32028,"text":"and next to me in the red hat,\nthat's my friend Paul Rice."},{"time":37168,"text":"So a couple of years\nafter this picture was taken,"},{"time":40614,"text":"Paul went into hospital\nfor some minor surgery,"},{"time":44475,"text":"and he developed\na superbug-related infection,"},{"time":48772,"text":"and he died."},{"time":50425,"text":"And I was truly shocked."},{"time":53198,"text":"He was a healthy guy in the prime of life."},{"time":56535,"text":"So there and then,"},{"time":57928,"text":"and actually with a lot of encouragement\nfrom a couple of TEDsters,"},{"time":61508,"text":"I declared my own\npersonal war on superbugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66365,"text":"So let's talk about superbugs\nfor a moment."},{"time":68735,"text":"The story actually starts in the 1940s"},{"time":72143,"text":"with the widespread\nintroduction of antibiotics."},{"time":75925,"text":"And since then,"},{"time":77348,"text":"drug-resistant bacteria\nhave continued to emerge,"},{"time":81908,"text":"and so we've been forced to develop\nnewer and newer drugs"},{"time":85353,"text":"to fight these new bacteria."},{"time":88061,"text":"And this vicious cycle\nactually is the origin of superbugs,"},{"time":93980,"text":"which is simply bacteria\nfor which we don't have effective drugs."},{"time":99474,"text":"I'm sure you'll recognize\nat least some of these superbugs."},{"time":103052,"text":"These are the more\ncommon ones around today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106158,"text":"Last year, around 700,000 people died"},{"time":110629,"text":"from superbug-related diseases."},{"time":113983,"text":"Looking to the future,"},{"time":117316,"text":"if we carry on on the path we're going,"},{"time":120476,"text":"which is basically a drugs-based\napproach to the problem,"},{"time":124126,"text":"the best estimate\nby the middle of this century"},{"time":126746,"text":"is that the worldwide death toll\nfrom superbugs will be 10 million."},{"time":132126,"text":"10 million."},{"time":133947,"text":"Just to put that in context,\nthat's actually more"},{"time":136782,"text":"than the number of people\nthat died of cancer worldwide last year."},{"time":140954,"text":"So it seems pretty clear\nthat we're not on a good road,"},{"time":145034,"text":"and the drugs-based approach\nto this problem is not working."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150247,"text":"I'm a physicist,"},{"time":152732,"text":"and so I wondered, could we take\na physics-based approach --"},{"time":156693,"text":"a different approach to this problem."},{"time":159590,"text":"And in that context,"},{"time":161146,"text":"the first thing we know for sure,"},{"time":163821,"text":"is that we actually know how to kill\nevery kind of microbe,"},{"time":167178,"text":"every kind of virus,"},{"time":168791,"text":"every kind of bacteria."},{"time":170809,"text":"And that's with ultraviolet light."},{"time":173505,"text":"We've actually known this\nfor more than 100 years."},{"time":176933,"text":"I think you all know\nwhat ultraviolet light is."},{"time":179593,"text":"It's part of a spectrum\nthat includes infrared,"},{"time":182656,"text":"it includes visible light,"},{"time":184126,"text":"and the short-wavelength part\nof this group is ultraviolet light."},{"time":189607,"text":"The key thing from our perspective here"},{"time":192720,"text":"is that ultraviolet light kills bacteria\nby a completely different mechanism"},{"time":197932,"text":"from the way drugs kill bacteria."},{"time":200605,"text":"So ultraviolet light is just as capable\nof killing a drug-resistant bacteria"},{"time":206417,"text":"as any other bacteria,"},{"time":208665,"text":"and because ultraviolet light\nis so good at killing all bugs,"},{"time":213167,"text":"it's actually used a lot these days\nto sterilize rooms,"},{"time":216326,"text":"sterilize working surfaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219398,"text":"What you see here is a surgical theater"},{"time":222250,"text":"being sterilized with germicidal\nultraviolet light."},{"time":227578,"text":"But what you don't see\nin this picture, actually,"},{"time":230079,"text":"is any people,"},{"time":231768,"text":"and there's a very good reason for that."},{"time":234028,"text":"Ultraviolet light\nis actually a health hazard,"},{"time":237639,"text":"so it can damage cells in our skin,"},{"time":239988,"text":"cause skin cancer,"},{"time":241443,"text":"it can damage cells in our eye,"},{"time":242978,"text":"cause eye diseases like cataract."},{"time":246490,"text":"So you can't use conventional,\ngermicidal, ultraviolet light"},{"time":249969,"text":"when there are people are around."},{"time":251722,"text":"And of course,"},{"time":252961,"text":"we want to sterilize mostly\nwhen there are people around."},{"time":256929,"text":"So the ideal ultraviolet light"},{"time":259620,"text":"would actually be able\nto kill all bacteria,"},{"time":263327,"text":"including superbugs,"},{"time":264887,"text":"but would be safe for human exposure."},{"time":268312,"text":"And actually that's where my physics\nbackground kicked into this story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273296,"text":"Together with my physics colleagues,"},{"time":275512,"text":"we realized there actually is a particular\nwavelength of ultraviolet light"},{"time":281611,"text":"that should kill all bacteria,"},{"time":284128,"text":"but should be safe for human exposure."},{"time":286928,"text":"That wavelength is called far-UVC light,"},{"time":290270,"text":"and it's just the short-wavelength part\nof the ultraviolet spectrum."},{"time":295375,"text":"So let's see how that would work."},{"time":298426,"text":"What you're seeing here\nis the surface of our skin,"},{"time":302259,"text":"and I'm going to superimpose on that\nsome bacteria in the air above the skin."},{"time":307536,"text":"Now we're going to see what happens"},{"time":309227,"text":"when conventional, germicidal,\nultraviolet light impinges on this."},{"time":315631,"text":"So what you see is,"},{"time":316805,"text":"as we know, germicidal light\nis really good at killing bacteria,"},{"time":322115,"text":"but what you also see"},{"time":323449,"text":"is that it penetrates\ninto the upper layers of our skin,"},{"time":326816,"text":"and it can damage\nthose key cells in our skin"},{"time":329392,"text":"which ultimately, when damaged,\ncan lead to skin cancer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334108,"text":"So let's compare now with far-UVC light --"},{"time":336980,"text":"same situation,"},{"time":338164,"text":"skin and some bacteria\nin the air above them."},{"time":342342,"text":"So what you're seeing now"},{"time":343618,"text":"is that again, far-UVC light's\nperfectly fine at killing bacteria,"},{"time":348438,"text":"but what far-UVC light can't do\nis penetrate into our skin."},{"time":353318,"text":"And there's a good,\nsolid physics reason for that:"},{"time":356057,"text":"far-UVC light is incredibly, strongly\nabsorbed by all biological materials,"},{"time":361445,"text":"so it simply can't go very far."},{"time":364680,"text":"Now, viruses and bacteria\nare really, really, really small,"},{"time":368661,"text":"so the far-UVC light can certainly\npenetrate them and kill them,"},{"time":373551,"text":"but what it can't do\nis penetrate into skin,"},{"time":376959,"text":"and it can't even penetrate\nthe dead-cell area"},{"time":379385,"text":"right at the very surface of our skin."},{"time":381815,"text":"So far-UVC light\nshould be able to kill bacteria,"},{"time":388161,"text":"but kill them safely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391397,"text":"So that's the theory."},{"time":392587,"text":"It should work, should be safe."},{"time":395921,"text":"What about in practice?"},{"time":397540,"text":"Does it really work?"},{"time":398715,"text":"Is it really safe?"},{"time":400599,"text":"So that's actually what our lab\nhas been working on"},{"time":403029,"text":"the past five or six years,"},{"time":405270,"text":"and I'm delighted to say the answer\nto both these questions"},{"time":408143,"text":"is an emphatic yes."},{"time":409348,"text":"Yes, it does work,"},{"time":410652,"text":"but yes, it is safe."},{"time":412460,"text":"So I'm delighted to say that,"},{"time":414257,"text":"but actually I'm not very\nsurprised to say that,"},{"time":416520,"text":"because it's purely the laws\nof physics at work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421911,"text":"So let's look to the future."},{"time":424070,"text":"I'm thrilled that we now have\na completely new weapon,"},{"time":429852,"text":"and I should say an inexpensive weapon,"},{"time":433340,"text":"in our fight against superbugs."},{"time":436447,"text":"For example,"},{"time":437719,"text":"I see far-UVC lights in surgical theaters."},{"time":441629,"text":"I see far-UVC lights\nin food preparation areas."},{"time":446046,"text":"And in terms of preventing\nthe spread of viruses,"},{"time":448930,"text":"I see far-UVC lights in schools,"},{"time":452126,"text":"preventing the spread of influenza,"},{"time":454673,"text":"preventing the spread of measles,"},{"time":456662,"text":"and I see far-UVC lights\nin airports or airplanes,"},{"time":460666,"text":"preventing the global spread\nof viruses like H1N1 virus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466015,"text":"So back to my friend Paul Rice."},{"time":468206,"text":"He was actually a well-known\nand well-loved local politician"},{"time":472125,"text":"in his and my hometown of Liverpool,"},{"time":474821,"text":"and they put up a statue in his memory\nin the center of Liverpool,"},{"time":479049,"text":"and there it is."},{"time":480368,"text":"But me,"},{"time":482582,"text":"I want Paul's legacy to be a major advance\nin this war against superbugs."},{"time":488002,"text":"Armed with the power of light,"},{"time":490091,"text":"that's actually within our grasp."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493297,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494472,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":499392,"text":"Chris Anderson: Stay up here, David,\nI've got a question for you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502535,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":505343,"text":"David, tell us where you're up to\nin developing this,"},{"time":509952,"text":"and what are the remaining obstacles\nto trying to roll out"},{"time":512923,"text":"and realize this dream?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":514678,"text":"David Brenner: Well, I think we now know\nthat it kills all bacteria,"},{"time":517893,"text":"but we sort of knew\nthat before we started,"},{"time":519972,"text":"but we certainly tested that."},{"time":522174,"text":"So we have to do lots and lots\nof tests about safety,"},{"time":524912,"text":"and so it's more about safety\nthan it is about efficacy."},{"time":528840,"text":"And we need to do short-term tests,"},{"time":531268,"text":"and we need to do long-term tests"},{"time":533295,"text":"to make sure you can't develop\nmelanoma many years on."},{"time":537494,"text":"So those studies\nare pretty well done at this point."},{"time":541850,"text":"The FDA of course is something\nwe have to deal with,"},{"time":547256,"text":"and rightly so,"},{"time":548655,"text":"because we certainly can't use this\nin the real world without FDA approval."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552766,"text":"CA: Are you trying\nto launch first in the US,"},{"time":555988,"text":"or somewhere else?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557772,"text":"DB: Actually, in a couple of countries."},{"time":559948,"text":"In Japan and in the US, both."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563873,"text":"CA: Have you been able to persuade\nbiologists, doctors,"},{"time":568502,"text":"that this is a safe approach?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570612,"text":"DB: Well, as you can imagine,\nthere is a certain skepticism"},{"time":573731,"text":"because everybody knows\nthat UV light is not safe."},{"time":577691,"text":"So when somebody comes along and says,"},{"time":579700,"text":"\"Well, this particular UV light is safe,\""},{"time":583060,"text":"there is a barrier to be crossed,"},{"time":584726,"text":"but the data are there,"},{"time":586940,"text":"and I think that's what\nwe're going to be standing on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590487,"text":"CA: Well, we wish you well."},{"time":592201,"text":"This is potentially such important work."},{"time":594130,"text":"Thank you so much\nfor sharing this with us."},{"time":596187,"text":"Thank you, David."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597362,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}